Package: nacleaner
Title: Simple Tools for Handling Missing Values
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Mason", "Good", email = "masongood@usf.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides three simple functions for working with missing values in data frames: reporting where NAs occur, dropping rows that contain them, and filling them with column statistics. Built as a final project for LIS 4370 R Programming.
